				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Melee's and Haste addiction<a name="69413"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 10 04 10:18 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>&lt;drags out dead horse&gt;
<br />

<br />
Melee's and haste addiction... They are just sick sick sick people.
<br />

<br />
Last night in a BoT group (guildies were slummin on an off day), we're pluggin away at the Jorl Militis' etc with a lvl 70 cleric tanking, a 64 cleric CH-ing, a rogue, me (66 bard), a zerker and a 60-61 chanter.
<br />

<br />
After the SoVallon from a buff bot that we ran over wears off, the zerker and rogue start whining &quot;Oooohhh... Ooooohhh... I need Haste.&quot;
<br />

<br />
I am scratching my head, Dance of the Blade (55%) is up, Warsong of Zek (60%) and Muse (+30%). 
<br />

<br />
The chanter drops Visions of Grandeur (58%) on the group, and the rogue and zerker both &quot;&lt;sigh&gt; yes haste&quot; in group chat.
<br />

<br />
I shake my head, give them both mental kicks in the arse, and pull a kriger to keep em busy.
<br />

<br />
They are almost as bad as the casters, &quot;Oh man KEI dropped, I need mana regen bad.&quot;
<br />
<i>The wind of Marr renews your spirit.
<br />
The wind of Marr renews your spirit.
<br />
The wind of Marr fades away.</i>
<br />

<br />
The bastiges.
<br />

<br />
Signed,
<br />
Unappreciated.</span></td>
