<br />

<br />
 What bugs me even more is how little people actually know about haste, especially stacking. I was grouped with a chanter and bst and they swore their hastes stacked with each other! I told them they didn't stack and they said look both icons are up so they stack. I tried to explain that my epic proc icon was up also + 2 songs with haste but they only get the highest haste spell and the overhaste so only 2 actually were stacking. All said and done I don't think they were conviced because everyone thinks there an  expert on haste. I don't know all the chanter haste spells but one time I had a chanter in my group that said he had 2 haste spells he could stack. I can't remember what they were but there were 2 icons up. I'm guessing one was a low level and the other a higher level haste spell that he figured stacked.
<br />

<br />
 And then there are the people that just don't understand how the haste actually works. They are convinced that using a 20 delay weapon with 50% haste would make it a 10 delay weapon. But just try to tell them that they are actually attacking 50% more and it would take 100% haste to theoretically reduce a 20 delay to 10. I generally get told I don't know what I'm talking about so now I just don't say anything.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
